<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 08 at 12:53AM CDT  by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT CRAIG AND SOUTHEASTERN NOWATA
COUNTIES THROUGH 130 AM CDT...
At 1253 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 10
miles north of New Alluwe, moving east at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.
Locations in or near the path include...
Vinita...                         Welch...
Bluejacket...                     White Oak...
Pyramid Corners...                Centralia...
Centrailia...
This includes Interstate 44 between mile markers 280 and 291.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
